title: Art from found materials, discarded and natural.pdf
description:
Crown | 1970 | Pdf | Eng | 244 pages | 29.7 MB

The Found Artist occupies a unique spot in the world of art for he is both a collector of things and a creator of things. His most prized acquisitions often have little or no commercial worth, but then price tags serve only to establish the  desirability of objects in terms of exchange, and may be completely unrelated to how the objects themselves are valued by an individual
